  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "By default, a random 30% of variants is held out during model training, with 10% representing the test data (\"k_folds = 10\") and 20% representing the validation data (\"validation_factor = 2\").",
    "Validation data is used to evaluate training progress and optimize hyperparameters (batch size, learning rate, L 1 and L 2 regularization penalties).",
    "Test data is used to assess final model performance.",
    "The held-out (test and validation) data can also be restricted to a user-specified subset of variants of a given mutation order if desired (\"holdout_orders\").",
    "In order to capture the uncertainty in fitness estimates, the training data is replaced with a random sample from the fitness error distribution of each variant (\"training_resample = True\")."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}